This paper proposes a technique for improving query processing in moving object indexing by exploiting the skew in velocity distribution. The paper discusses the use of principal components analysis (PCA) and k-means clustering to identify dominant velocity axes (DVAs) and create a moving object index based on each DVA. The paper also discusses the implementation of the technique on two representative index structures, the TPR*-tree and the Bx-tree. Based on this information, the most likely sub-category is cs.DB (databases), followed by cs.IR (information retrieval), cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.AI (artificial intelligence), and cs.CV (computer vision).
